<br>
And thus we get the real issue with Epic Weapons, and why they were one of the worst things that ever happened to EQ. VI doesn't want every Paladin over level 50 to have a nice flaming portable BBQ sword. That means somewhere someone who puts in the time and effort to get one is going to come up dry, that is why there is a bottleneck.<br>
<br>
They did an experiment with the rogue and monk classes by removing all serious bottlenecks from their epic quests. Look what happened, every 50+ monk/rogue with 12 friends has their epic. It's trivial, it doesn't mean anything, it cheapens the idea of an &quot;epic quest&quot; for every single one of them. Do you really want the Paladin epic to be considered trivial? Didn't think so. Do you want to feel like you acomplished something special, that your time, effort, and dedication were well rewarded? Yea, is what I thought. So in the mean time stop bitching about how hard the Paladin epic is, because it isn't. And stop whining about how awful the book bottleneck is, because it serves a purpose.<br>
