<br>
My issue with the current system is, to me, it doesn't feel like I have that reasonable chance.<br>
<br>
For perspective, to kill Lucan: took me about 3 weeks to get enough friends notified and agreeing to be able to take down Lucan.  It then took me 3 weekends to finally get a spawn.  Every time we found he was up, someone else was either killing him moments after spawn, or pulled him while we were organizing.  He appears to be an eight hour spawn, and we normally attempted 4 or 5 spawns a weekend.  I'm not uber, nor is my guild, nor are the people I know.<br>
<br>
Most of my guildmates are either grossly below 52 or over it, and thus any Naggy/Vox raids I join cannot be my own guild.  With the rarity of the drops, and senority/predistination plans on most raids, I will be highly unlikely that I will get drops.  I know less about the Kunark dragons, but I know my guild does not have the strength to attempt them, and I imagine joining other groups' raids would also leave me even smaller than normal chance at these two books.<br>
<br>
Things like the Shaman epic, where the trials are a variety, ranging over assorted levels, and almost all triggered spawns, seem very appealing.  The trial of patience seems like it is really appropriate <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
The mage epic, while having numerous difficult spawns, if I remember correctly (been a while since I've read that one) virtually every spawn is triggered or normally up.<br>
Monk epic, as has been mentioned, you can do with 20 of your closest friends in a weekend.<br>
Druid epic - sure, make me run over the known world!<br>
<br>
Make me kill lots of hard things, make me talk to people, make me a currier, make me work, but don't make me wait around for 7day nontriggered spawns that rarely drop the items I need 2 of.  Even if it still takes me the same many months to complete this altered epic as camping Naggy/Vox/Kunark dragons would, I would prefer /doing/ something those months and known I was working toward the goal, rather than just praying the book dropped and I got lucky on the /random (if the recipient isn't predetermined).<br>
<br>
Just my opinion.<br>
