Ok, then what is your counter proposal?  Would it be better if the FD required neither levels nor friends?  I was 60 before I got my first book, and 60 for months before I finished it.<br>
<br>
And sorry to contradict you, but I had people go out of their way into the wee hours to help me get my FD.  People help Shamans and Monks get their Epics because the mobs are spawned, are quick to finish, and always drop what is needed.  In essence they help them because it isn't much of a burden at all.  Clerics and other classes may get help because in addition to the ease of the quest the end result is a tangible benefit to the guild as a whole and even to the individuals assisting.<br>
<br>
The FD is neither guaranteed, easy (in relation to other epic mobs), fast, nor of great importance to the guild or to others.<br>
<br>
So, why did they help me?<br>
<br>
Because of the respect and friendships established between us in the fantasy world of Norrath.<br>
<br>
And THAT is was made the accomplishment of the quest special to me.  It wasn't the stats, the bash ability, the proc, the graphics, or the fact that I 'had my epic'.  Dozens of people (over the span of months and many hours raiding) assembled to help me complete my quest for no reason other than to show their gratitude towards me.<br>
<br>
