<br>
Paladins/SKs -- can't use epic on raids. Switch to a non-proc'ing 2h, or non-proc'ing 1h + shield...<br>
<br>
Warriors -- don't bother, quest takes too long, pick up a pair of TOV swords instead.<br>
<br>
Important epics? Cleric/enchanter/mage. Those are the ones we seem to actively work on assisting, the others require the majority of the work to be done by the individual on their own time and for the raids to not occur when there is something scheduled -- TOV/Tormax/Dain/Yelinak/WW/etc.<br>
<br>
So, that being said... why would I want to get the FD? For the status symbol? I'll pass on that bit of egotism. I don't want my epic because it's &quot;the epic&quot;. I would want it to make myself more useful to my friends and to the guild.<br>
<br>
There are plenty of ways I can do that, and none of them require that one item. Now clerics, the epic adds a very vital and useful ability that is unique to their epic. If the paladin epic version 2.0 has &quot;AE Silence for 20 seconds&quot; as a trigger/proc... then I'd sink my time into it and sink the time of my friends and guild as well, because of the ability that I would have to help them.<br>
<br>
However, I don't buy into the &quot;if it didn't have the bottleneck, everyone would have it&quot; part.<br>
<br>
If you're right then I'm sure that everyone has a Qeynos Badge of Honor. I mean, there's no real bottleneck in the quest, anyone with a couple of friends of high enough level can complete the quest. Some minor timers involved but nothing at all restrictive. Most of it can even be done by one person, the others just make it easier and more certain (since it doesn't work like the ring, if you screw up you have to start from the beginning).<br>
<br>
QBoH is a perfect example of a quest which is difficult (there's too many ways to screw it up or have it screwed up) but requires only a modicum of effort applied into it... and a lot of time and personal investment.<br>
<br>
Let's take another example more dear to our hearts -- Divine Might. There are no bottlenecks to this quest, other than bone respawn times if multiple people want to do it at the same time. One person can acheive most of this quest on their own... and yet there are a lot of pallies who don't have this. (I say this because I've got everything for this quest except for a diamond, the &quot;special&quot; fire gem, and the Kedge bone... which I _could_ theoretically get myself, just not with a large survival chance).<br>
<br>
Just my opinion.<br>
<br>
--Jas <p><table align=center width=80%><tr><td NOWRAP>
